<title>SWITZERLAND: Richemont details 1996/97 results.</title>
<headline>Richemont details 1996/97 results.</headline>
<dateline>ZUG, Switzerland 1997-06-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to March 31, 1997</p>
<p>(million Stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Net sales revenue	    4,755.8	   vs 4,306.9</p>
<p> Operating Profit	     954.2	     vs 798.9</p>
<p>Profit attrib to</p>
<p> unitholders		    302.9	     vs 316.1</p>
<p> Earnings per unit (Stg)    52.75	     vs 55.05</p>
<p> Div per unit (Stg)	   9.40		vs 8.00</p>
<p>Revenue per segment</p>
<p>   Tobacco			3,300.1	   vs 2,840.1</p>
<p>   Luxury goods		 1,455.7	   vs 1,466.8</p>
<p>Oper profit per segment</p>
<p>   Tobacco			795.9	     vs 587.0</p>
<p>   Luxury goods		 243.3	     vs 249.7</p>
<p>   Other (loss)		-2.0		 vs -7.0</p>
<p>Oper profit (loss) from</p>
<p> assoc. undertakings	 -83.0		vs -30.8</p>
<p>   Tobacco			14.1		vs 18.7</p>
<p>   Media interests	   -81.0		vs -46.3</p>
<p>   NAR Group*		  -16.1		vs -3.2</p>
<p>* Includes principal subsidiary Hanover Direct, a U.S.-based specialty retailer</p>
<p>-- Note: Full company name is Compagnie Financiere Richemont AG.</p>
<p>-- Zurich Editorial +41 1 631 7340</p>
